<br>
“Names?” She repeated. He grinned.<br>
<br>
“We can only call the kid ‘baby Luthor’ for so long before they start to get resentful,” he smirked. “I’m open to any names besides Clark.” She smiled, but he noticed that it didn’t reach her eyes. “What’s wrong?” She sighed.<br>
<br>
“You know me entirely too well for someone I haven’t been going out with for that long,” she commented.<br>
<br>
“And because I know you so well, I know that you just said that to avoid answering what I just asked you,” he countered. She had a very serious look on her face and she brought her hand up to caress his cheek. “Now you have me worried. What’s going on?”<br>
<br>
“They,” she paused, trying not to get too emotional, but she could feel the lump in her throat forming. “They don’t know what effects the poison is going to have on the baby.” Her lip quivered and she wouldn’t look him in the eye. “We may not even need to get to the naming stage.” Lex leaned over and kissed her forehead. He grinned as he pulled back.<br>
<br>
“That’s the most ridiculous thing I’ve ever heard,” he said. Chloe let out a very unladylike snort and Lex chuckled. “After all, look at their gene pool. There’s also the fact that the pregnancy test showed positive so soon.”<br>
<br>
“I asked about that, they said it depended on the woman,” Chloe responded. Lex grinned.<br>
<br>
“Exactly. You’re a fighter, I’m a fighter,” Lex started and Chloe rolled her eyes, effectively making her dizzy, but it was worth it to see the look on Lex’s face. “Our kids will be fighters too,” he finished in a soft and comforting voice. Chloe arched an eyebrow.<br>
<br>
“Kids? As in plural?” Chloe called him on his previous statement. He shrugged.<br>
<br>
“We’re still young and have lots of breeding years left, just not ruling out any possibilities,” he smirked.<br>
<br>
“Jerk,” she said kiddingly and hit his arm. He laughed.<br>
<br>
“You’re assuming that I’m joking,” Lex smiled.<br>
<br>
“Of course you’re joking, I’m only sixteen,” she said.<br>
<br>
“My great grandmother was only fifteen when she had her first child.”<br>
<br>
“Well, that’s different,” Chloe said. “That was back in the days when people got married that young too.” Lex arched an eyebrow.<br>
<br>
“Your point being?” He asked. Chloe playfully narrowed her eyes at his serious tone, but chose not to respond. “So how long are they keeping you here?” He asked. Chloe groaned.<br>
<br>
“At least another day, they want to make sure all of the bad stuff is out of my system,” she answered. He nodded.<br>
<br>
“I’m sure Kent will want to see you, he and Lana have been out in the waiting room all this time.” Lex really didn’t want Chloe to allow Clark to see her, especially not without him being in the room, but he knew that if he started acting jealous and possessive it would make her pull away, and he couldn’t risk that, especially now.<br>
<br>
“Wow!” She exclaimed. “And you’re actually telling me this?” She smiled broadly. “I have the best boyfriend in the world.” Lex laughed and leaned over to kiss her.<br>
<br>
“No argument,” he said, conveniently leaving out that he knew Clark was in love with her.<br>
<br>
~*~*~*~*~<br>
<br>
Lex reluctantly left Chloe to go tell Clark and Lana that it was their turn to see her. Before all of this happened, he would have felt more comfortable with Lana being in the room too, but now it seemed that she was just as anxious to have Chloe break up with him and go out with Clark as Clark was. He frowned. He knew under the current circumstances that Chloe would never leave him; he just needed to make sure that the circumstances didn’t change. He walked over to where Clark and Lana sat and they looked up at his foreboding presence.<br>
<br>
“She wants to see you,” he muttered. Clark alone stood up and Lex winced. He motioned to Lana. “You too. I think she’s getting too tired to take anymore separate visitors.” Lana nodded and stood up. She had been hoping that Clark could get some alone time with Chloe, but she wasn’t going to cross Lex’s path tonight. Clark and Lana disappeared down the hallway and Lex walked over to where Gabe was still sitting. He offered no sort of emotion.<br>
<br>
“Chloe asked me to give you a ride home,” Lex said in a neutral voice. Gabe glanced at the clock, nodded, and stood up.<br>
<br>
“Thanks.”<br>
<br>
~*~*~*~*~<br>
<br>
Clark and Lana entered Chloe’s room. Lana smiled to herself as Clark rushed to Chloe’s side. Chloe smiled weakly.<br>
<br>
“Hey guys,” she greeted. Clark brushed the top of her hair with her hand and she pulled back a little, but tried not to make it too obvious. After all, he was still her friend, and that could have just been a friendly gesture. Clark and Lana were both smiling. Clark held Chloe’s hand and began to lace his fingers with hers.<br>
<br>
“Are you doing okay? Your dad said you were still pretty dizzy,” he said with concern. Chloe laughed.<br>
<br>
“Tell me about it, I don’t think I have anything left to puke up,” she said. Clark and Lana both jokingly made ‘eww’ faces.<br>
<br>
“I was worried about you Chlo,” Clark admitted. She grinned.<br>
<br>
“I’ll be all right Clark. With any luck, I might even get to go home tomorrow night,” Chloe responded. Lana frowned slightly. It worked to her tactical advantage to have Chloe in the hospital a little longer so Clark could dote over her and win her back.<br>
<br>
“Well, don’t rush things,” Lana said and both heads turned toward her. “I mean, we wouldn’t want you to think you’re all better and then have to come right back here.” Clark smiled and nodded, turning his attention back to Chloe.<br>
<br>
“She’s right. And you know, I’ll be here to take care of you, whatever you need,” he added. Lana smiled to herself again. Clark had picked up on that much quicker than she thought he would. Chloe smiled.<br>
<br>
“I know you will Clark, but it’s not necessary,” Chloe said. He shook his head.<br>
<br>
“We’re still friends Chloe and friends take care of each other,” he reasoned. She nodded.<br>
<br>
“Okay,” she agreed. Clark looked at her struggle to keep her eyes open and he chuckled.<br>
<br>
“You’re pretty tired, we should get going,” he said as he stood up, but he still held her hand. He quickly glanced over at Lana, who was giving him a ‘go on’ look. He bent down and kissed Chloe’s cheek. “I love you Chlo.”<br>
<br>
