<br>
“Chloe told me what you said to her,” Lex elaborated. Clark looked down at his feet.<br>
<br>
“I meant it,” he responded, raising his eyes to Lex’s in a challenging manner. Lex gritted his teeth and nodded once.<br>
<br>
“I know you did,” he said as he took a small step closer. “You’re incredibly lucky that she thinks you meant only as a friend,” Lex said menacingly.<br>
<br>
“I’ll have to go clear that up the,” Clark said as he side-stepped out of Lex’s way. Clark could practically see the imaginary steam coming from Lex’s ears.<br>
<br>
“It won’t matter Clark, she won’t leave me,” Lex said with confidence.<br>
<br>
“Why do you think that?” Clark asked in an almost mocking tone. “After all, she hasn’t been going out with you for that long, and she was in love with me for years.”<br>
<br>
“Chloe doesn’t strike me as a woman who would leave the future father of her children,” Lex half-grinned. Clark started laughing, but only because he hadn’t been told what the situation was.<br>
<br>
“And you think it will be you?” Clark continued laughing.<br>
<br>
“It’s already me Clark,” Lex responded in a serious tone, giving Clark a minute to digest what he had just said. Clark’s face looked like his world had just collapsed.<br>
<br>
“What?” He asked disbelievingly, making sure he had heard him correctly. Lex sighed. If this boy wasn’t his rival for Chloe’s affections, then he might feel sorry for him.<br>
<br>
“Chloe’s pregnant Clark,” he said, expecting a little more of Clark’s life to crumble and for the young man to recognize defeat. Instead, Clark looked angry and had a suspicious gleam in his eyes. Clark ran his hands over his face.<br>
<br>
“God Lex! You did this on purpose didn’t you?!” He yelled. Lex tried hard to hide the smirk that spread across his features, but he didn’t quite succeed. “Why?!” Clark continued. “To make sure she wouldn’t come back to me?!” Lex raised an eyebrow.<br>
<br>
“She was never with you to begin with,” Lex paused. “But essentially yes,” he admitted. “Chloe’s the first person I’ve actually loved since my mother died,” he tried to explain. “I couldn’t risk her leaving me because of you or any other high school schmuck who secretly fawns all over her.”<br>
<br>
Lex didn’t see or anticipate the fist that connected with his face, leaving him bleeding and unconscious on the barn floor.<br>
<br>
~*~*~*~*~<br>
<br>
Clark ran outside the barn and saw that the truck was gone. It was dangerous to use his abilities in the middle of the day, but he had to get to Chloe, he had to tell her what was going on. He ran as fast as he could to the hospital and rushed to Chloe’s room once he got there.<br>
<br>
“Chloe!” He said a little too loudly, waking her from her sleep. She looked at him blankly for a moment.<br>
<br>
“What’s going on?” She asked, concern lacing the notes of her voice. He swooped down and gave her a giant hug. Chloe was confused. Why all of the affection all of a sudden? She pulled away from him. “What’s wrong Clark?” He ran a hand through his hair, his other hand still gripping onto hers for dear life. He was shaking a little.<br>
<br>
“Chloe, it’s Lex,” he started. Her eyes grew wide in panic.<br>
<br>
“What happened?!” She asked, feeling a sudden terror run through her body. He shook his head.<br>
<br>
“He did this on purpose Chlo,” he said. She looked confused.<br>
<br>
“He did what on purpose?” She asked and he sat down next to her on the bed. He took a deep breath, which Chloe knew was never a sign of good news with him. He gently placed his hand on her stomach.<br>
<br>
“He got you pregnant on purpose, so you wouldn’t leave him,” he explained. Chloe’s expression told Clark that she didn’t believe him.<br>
<br>
“Clark…” she said, only to be cut off by the insistent ‘I’m telling you the truth’ look on his face. “Why would he do that?” She asked, still not entirely believing what Clark was telling her. He frowned.<br>
<br>
“I don’t know, it’s like he’s obsessed or something,” Clark answered. “But he doesn’t like losing just with regular stuff, imagine that like a zillion times worse for losing the woman he thinks he’s in love with.” Chloe glared at him.<br>
<br>
“Lex does love me Clark, he doesn’t just think it,” she argued. He leaned in closer to her and brushed some hair away from her face with his fingers, his other hand still entwined with hers. He shook his head and pulled back a little.<br>
<br>
“I would never say this to you otherwise, but I think you…” He was about to tell her that he thought she should get rid of the pregnancy or at least that she should dump Lex and let him help raise the child, but he paused when he saw the questioning look on her face. She was staring at his knuckles, which he only now realized were covered in Lex’s blood.<br>
Her face paled and her voice shook when she spoke.<br>
<br>
“What did you do?”<br>
