<br>
“Clark?” She asked again. Clark kept his gaze down. He realized that he should feel some remorse for what he had done, and in a way he did, just not in any way he could explain to Chloe so that she’d believe him.<br>
<br>
“I lost my temper,” he admitted in a quiet voice. She stared at him disbelievingly.<br>
<br>
“You lost your temper?” The temporary feeling of astonishment at his previous words was being replaced by anger. “You have blood on you Clark! Did you hurt him?!” She raised her voice almost to a yell and he winced. He absently started stroking her hand with his thumb.<br>
<br>
“I don’t know,” he said honestly as he dared to look up into her eyes. “I hit him and then I came here to tell you what I found out.”<br>
<br>
“How many times did you hit him?” Chloe asked, not really wanting to know the answer. Clark shook his head.<br>
<br>
“Just once Chlo, I promise.” He sighed and found himself getting lost in her eyes. He mentally chided himself. ‘You could have prevented all of this from happening if you had just admitted the truth to yourself sooner,’ he thought. “I’m sure he’ll be fine,” he said reassuringly.<br>
<br>
“He’d better be,” Chloe answered in a stern voice that caught Clark off guard. He stared at her lovingly.<br>
<br>
“Chloe, I know you think you love him,” Clark began. Chloe opened her mouth to interrupt, but Clark put a finger up to her lips. “But can you honestly say that you love someone who would intentionally get you pregnant without you knowing about it? Just so he can eliminate the competition?”<br>
<br>
“He doesn’t have any competition,” she said bluntly. She didn’t believe what Clark was telling her, and now she was trying to ward off all of the terrible things going through her head about how hurt Lex was. Clark grinned and started stroking his fingers up and down her arm.<br>
<br>
“Chloe, I know that I haven’t always been there for you, but I love you. That’s why I came to tell you what happened.” He had to restrain himself from leaning in and kissing her. He knew that in her state she was more likely to punch him than to reciprocate the kiss.<br>
<br>
“I know you love me Clark,” she said, exasperated. “You’re my best friend, of course you love me. I love you too.” Clark’s face lit up and he smiled brightly.<br>
<br>
“You do?” He asked, his voice full of hope. She nodded once.<br>
<br>
“And for a while, I even thought that I loved you as more than a friend,” she admitted. Much to her surprise, not even a little blush rose to her cheeks. “But, now that I know what that kind of love is really like…” she trailed off and shook her head, immediately regretting the motion with the wave of nausea that swept through her. “I’m sorry if I gave you a hard time about Lana, I know that you two will be happy together when you finally get around to asking her out.” Clark looked like he was in shock. He hadn’t been expecting that.<br>
<br>
“Chloe, you don’t understand, I don’t love Lana like that, I love you,” Clark rambled out. Chloe grinned.<br>
<br>
“I know what you meant, but I don’t feel that way about you, not anymore,” she said, trying to let him down easy. She had a sneaking suspicion that Lana was the only reason he had these ‘new found feelings’. She figured a change of topic would be the best way to kill two birds with one stone. “I’m tired. Do you think I can see Lex before I go back to sleep?” She asked. Clark frowned at her dismissal of his admission, but a nagging voice inside his head kept telling him that he could win her back if he played his cards right.<br>
<br>
“Uh, I don’t know if that’s such a good idea,” Clark said. She narrowed her eyes at him.<br>
<br>
“He was bleeding,” she observed, motioning to his hand with her head. “You brought him to the hospital to get fixed up, right?” Clark didn’t answer. “Right?” She asked a little bit louder. He refused to look her in the eyes. “You left him there?!” Now Chloe was really angry. “What’s the matter with you?!”<br>
<br>
“No, no, he’s just waiting for a doctor right now,” Clark lied. He wasn’t very good at it, but it sounded convincing enough. He could certainly get home and then back to the hospital with Lex in time for Chloe to not know he lied. He stood up. “Do you want me to go check on him?” Chloe pushed her feeling that Clark was being less than honest with her aside and nodded.<br>
<br>
“Please,” she said. She was getting tired, but she doubted that she’d be able to get any sleep if she didn’t know for sure that Lex was actually all right. She watched Clark leave the room and then closed her eyes. ‘Please let him be okay.’<br>
<br>
~*~*~*~*~<br>
<br>
Clark was walking toward the exit when he caught a glimpse of his mom out of the corner of his eye.<br>
<br>
“Mom!” He said a little louder than he needed to, so he could get her attention. She turned to look at him. He walked over to her, and the closer he got, he could see that her expression was that of pure worry. Clark frowned. He gave her hug. “Is everything okay?” She shook her head and wrapped her arms across her body.<br>
<br>
“I found Lex in the barn,” she began, unsure of how to break the news to her son that his friend was injured. “He was just lying there and there was so much blood,” she said, and then briefly covered her mouth with her hand. “I’m so sorry Clark, one of the horses must have gotten free or something.” Clark didn’t know what to say. He couldn’t very well tell her that he had hit him because he stole his girl and got her pregnant. Better to pretend that he didn’t know what had happened, at least for now.<br>
<br>
“Wow,” he said, managing to pull off a surprised look quite successfully. “Is he going to be all right?” His mom ran a hand through her hair.<br>
<br>
“I don’t know honey. The paramedics said that his vitals were strong, so I think that’s probably a good sign.” She paused. “Do you know why he would be in our barn?” Clark frowned and shrugged.<br>
<br>
“He probably came to see me, but I’ve been here with Chloe,” he lied again. He was getting better at it. Although, it helped that he hadn’t told his parents anything about Chloe and Lex’s relationship and everything surrounding it. She seemed to believe him and patted his arm.<br>
<br>
“These past couple of days have been really hard for you haven’t they?” She asked in a comforting voice. He looked at the floor. They had been difficult, but not for the reasons she thought.<br>
<br>
“Yeah,” he said.<br>
<br>
“Well, don’t worry. Chloe and Lex are both fighters. They’ll be fine.”<br>
<br>
~*~*~*~*~<br>
<br>
Chloe fell asleep waiting for Clark to come back and give her news about Lex. She didn’t know how much time had passed, but she was awoken by a familiar female voice.<br>
<br>
“Chloe?” A hand reached out and gently touched her own, prompting Chloe to slowly open her eyes.<br>
<br>
“Mrs. Kent,” she acknowledged. Clark’s mom gave Chloe a sympathetic grin and sat down next to Chloe.<br>
<br>
“How are you feeling?” She asked. Chloe noticed that she seemed genuinely concerned and figured that Clark hadn’t clued his parents in to what had been going on.<br>
<br>
“A little better, they said I might be able to go home later,” Chloe answered with a little bit of hope in her voice.<br>
<br>
“Well, take it easy. You have a tendency not to rest when you’re not being forced to,” Martha observed. Chloe smiled.<br>
<br>
“So I’ve been told,” she responded.<br>
<br>
“Clark told me to tell you that Lex should be fine,” Martha said. “I understand that you two have become friends.” Contentment passed over Chloe’s face and she grinned.<br>
<br>
“More than that,” she said confidently. Martha looked confused and almost shocked.<br>
<br>
“What do you mean?” She asked, making sure she heard what she thought she heard.<br>
<br>
“We’re dating,” Chloe confirmed. ‘Well, sort of,’ she thought. Martha’s mouth dropped open a little and she suddenly appeared very concerned.<br>
<br>
“Are you sure that’s such a good idea sweetie?” She asked in her best motherly voice. Chloe almost laughed, but was able to restrain herself. She couldn’t hide the smile that came across her lips though.<br>
<br>
“It’s okay, really,” Chloe stressed the last part. “I’m a little surprised that Clark didn’t tell you.” A myriad of thoughts were running through Martha’s head and not one of them was good. She had a feeling that her son had been lying to her about Lex being at the barn, but had decided to trust him. Now she felt that was a bad decision. He had hurt Lex. It would not have been difficult, given his abilities, but the reason hadn’t been clear until Chloe told her that she and Lex were dating. She could only see a very bad outcome to the entire situation.<br>
<br>
“Well, I’m sure he had a good reason,” she said as she stood up to leave. “If there’s anything you need, be sure to let me know. Okay Chloe?” Chloe grinned and nodded. Martha went to find her son. They needed to have a talk.<br>
<br>
~*~*~*~*~<br>
<br>
Lex strayed back to consciousness and squinted his eyes at the bright hospital lights. The last thing he remembered was being in the Kents’ barn arguing with Clark, but now he was in the hospital and in a great deal of pain. He groaned, and a nurse checking his chart looked up.<br>
<br>
“Good to see you awake Mr. Luthor,” she commented. She was in her late thirties and from the way she carried herself, Lex could tell that she would not be intimidated easily. He glared at her.<br>
<br>
“Are you in any pain?” She asked. Pain was an understatement. “You had to receive some surgical services, but they didn’t give you any pain medication because you were out cold,” she said. Well, that certainly explained things. Lex continued to glare at her, but she rolled her eyes and set his chart down. “I’ll go get your doctor.” She turned on her heel and left him in the room. A few minutes later Dr. Schafer came into the room. Lex’s eyes widened at the site of her. Someone he recognized, Chloe’s doctor, thank God.<br>
<br>
“I’m going to give you some morphine for the pain,” she started and he shook his head. She gave him a questioning look.<br>
<br>
“No narcotics,” he said simply. She nodded in understanding.<br>
<br>
“Alright. I’m sure we can come up with something else,” she said and gave him a grin. “Your girlfriend has been asking about you. Do you want me to give her a message?”<br>
<br>
“Can I see her?” Lex tried to raise himself up to a sitting position, but his head hurt so much. He attempted to rub his jaw, but realized that it was bandaged. Dr. Schafer grimaced.<br>
<br>
“It’s going to hurt for a while. You’re very lucky that only minimal reconstructive surgery was needed. Do you remember what happened?” She asked. He furrowed his brow in thought and then shook his head. “It’s okay, that’s to be expected.”<br>
<br>
“Can I see her?” Lex asked again, realizing that she hadn’t answered him the first time.<br>
<br>
“I was planning on releasing her this evening, maybe I can have someone bring her by in a wheelchair or something,” she said sympathetically. “Has she talked to you about the options yet?” He raised an eyebrow at her. “Regarding the pregnancy.”<br>
<br>
“There are no options,” he replied in a neutral voice that came across somewhat threatening. “We’re keeping our child.” She frowned; it obviously wasn’t the answer she was hoping for.<br>
<br>
“With all due respect, I think you need to look at the big picture. Ms. Sullivan is a beautiful and intelligent young woman. But, she’s only sixteen. If you make her go through with this pregnancy, she could end up resenting you and herself for the rest of your lives.” Lex was getting angry, and he was still in a lot of pain. It wasn’t the best combination for keeping his temper under control.<br>
<br>
“Chloe is beautiful and intelligent. I have no doubts that our child will be also. I have no intention of ever letting either one of them go. And if you try to convince her to get rid of the baby, I’ll make sure you regret it,” he threatened. His words were like ice and Dr. Schafer swallowed in fear. “Do you understand?” She nodded and stepped further away from him.<br>
<br>
“I’ll have the nurse bring some pain medication in,” she barely managed speak without tripping over her words. She turned and left the room and Lex laid his head back against the pillow. He didn’t understand why everyone was trying to stand in the way of his relationship with Chloe. He almost felt bad about what he had told Clark. He hadn’t planned to get Chloe pregnant, but he couldn’t help using Clark’s belief that he did against him. He just wanted him to see that Chloe was his, would always be his; but the pain radiating from his head and down his body was starting to make him wonder if Clark Kent wasn’t a more formidable opponent for Chloe’s affections than he had believed.<br>
<br>
~*~*~*~*~<br>
<br>
A few hours later, a hospital volunteer peeked inside Lex’s room. His eyes were closed, but he sensed her presence.<br>
<br>
“What?” He asked. The girl smiled.<br>
<br>
“Are you up for visitors?” She asked. He opened his eyes and looked at her, then looked past her to see the front part of a wheelchair in the hallway. He grinned and nodded. The girl pushed Chloe into Lex’s room and positioned the chair so that it was next to the bed. “Just call a nurse when you’re ready to go back to your room,” she said and then left. Chloe reached out a hand and clasped onto Lex’s arm.<br>
<br>
“How are you doing?” She asked. She couldn’t see his injuries, but if the bandages on his skull were any indication, Clark must have hit him several times with some sort of farm equipment. She didn’t want to think about that now. She was just glad he was alive. He grinned.<br>
<br>
“I’m a fighter,” he answered in a quirky manner. She smiled. There was a little bit of a pause in the conversation as their fingers caressed each other’s. “Dr. Schafer wanted to know if you had gone over the options with me,” he said quietly. As much as he wanted her to keep the pregnancy, it was her decision, and legally he could do nothing about it.<br>
<br>
“Yeah,” she answered in the same volume. She looked down and he got worried.<br>
<br>
‘Crap,’ he thought. ‘She doesn’t want to have the baby, or the poison affected the baby somehow, or…’<br>
<br>
“Lex, I know it’s only a couple days along, and I don’t expect you to be happy with this, but I,” she paused and he shut his eyes and cringed. This couldn’t be happening. “I don’t think I could ever get rid of it,” she said in a small voice. He opened his eyes.<br>
<br>
“I didn’t catch that last part,” he lied. She still wasn’t looking at his face, so she couldn’t see the grin that was developing there.<br>
<br>
“I don’t think I could ever get rid of it,” she said a little louder. He smiled and she looked up to see his reaction.<br>
<br>
“God Chloe, I’d kiss you if I wasn’t in so much pain.”<br>
