<br>
“Well it’s about time is all I have to say,” Jonathan said proudly. Martha turned her head and shot him a glare, causing him to shrink down in his chair. “Of course, you should be careful about that sort of thing son, especially given your abilities.” He looked at his wife to make sure that was enough of an apologetic statement to her.<br>
<br>
“You could have killed him Clark,” she said, lowering the volume of her voice a little. “We’ll be lucky if he doesn’t press charges.” She wanted him to know how serious this was.<br>
<br>
“You don’t know what happened Mom,” Clark tried to explain.<br>
<br>
“You found out that Chloe was dating Lex,” Martha replied, thinking that was the reason. Clark shook his head.<br>
<br>
“Chloe’s dating Lex?” Jonathan asked, clearly confused and somewhat horrified.<br>
<br>
“I already knew that,” he admitted. Martha’s mouth dropped open. “I found out that he got her pregnant on purpose to keep her from coming back to me,” he said quietly, knowing that his parents wouldn’t react well to that news.<br>
<br>
“What?!” Jonathan yelled and jumped out of his chair. “That son of a bitch!” He started stomping toward the door, but Martha stopped him.<br>
<br>
“Does she know this?” She asked.<br>
<br>
“I told her, but I don’t think she believed me,” Clark said. Martha closed her eyes and sighed.<br>
<br>
“I don’t know how I should punish you Clark,” she finally said. Jonathan arched an eyebrow.<br>
<br>
“Punish him?” He asked incredulously.<br>
<br>
“He punched Lex and knocked him out. Lex had to have reconstructive surgery Jonathan,” she explained.<br>
<br>
“So?” He asked, not impressed with the reasons for the punishment.<br>
<br>
“If it were anyone else besides Lex Luthor?” She asked. He huffed and stood by his son.<br>
<br>
“Anyone else besides Lex Luthor wouldn’t have stolen her away from Clark and gotten her pregnant intentionally,” he argued, but then seeing the stern expression on her face he relented and turned to face his son. “Sorry.” Clark nodded.<br>
<br>
“It’s okay, I was expecting it,” he said as he sat down.<br>
<br>
~*~*~*~*~<br>
<br>
“Hey sweetheart,” Gabe greeted Chloe as he walked into her hospital room. She was already dressed and sitting in a wheelchair with a volunteer standing behind her. She smiled and he chuckled. “Not anxious to get out of here or anything are you?” He asked sarcastically. She shook her head lightly.<br>
<br>
“I’m really, really sick of hospitals. I just want to go home,” she answered. He smiled.<br>
<br>
“I can take her,” he said to the volunteer.<br>
<br>
“I’m sorry sir, but it’s hospital…”<br>
<br>
“Policy,” he interrupted and nodded his head. “This hospital seems to have a lot of those. Alright, well, let’s get going then.”<br>
<br>
“Wait,” Chloe said. Gabe turned around to face her again.<br>
<br>
“Forget something?”<br>
<br>
“No, I just want to stop and tell Lex that I’m leaving,” she answered.<br>
<br>
“Did he go to the cafeteria or something?” Gabe asked, confused as to why Lex would be at the hospital and not in her room. ‘Not that I mind,’ he thought to himself.<br>
<br>
“No, he’s in his room,” Chloe said, earning a questioning look from her father. She sighed. “He got in a fight with Clark yesterday.” Her dad arched an eyebrow.<br>
<br>
“And now he’s in the hospital?” Gabe asked in a surprised tone. ‘Good for Clark,’ he cheered silently.<br>
<br>
“Don’t seem too happy about it or anything Dad,” Chloe said, noticing the bemused expression that had formed on her father’s face.<br>
<br>
“Ah, sorry,” he said, a little embarrassed that Chloe had noticed.<br>
<br>
“So, can we stop by his room before we leave?” She asked. He frowned and nodded his head.<br>
<br>
“Not for long, you’re supposed to be resting,” he said. She smiled in agreement. As they made their way to Lex’s room, Gabe was having trouble suppressing his pride in Clark for standing up to Lex. He didn’t know all of the details, but he suspected that it had something to do with his daughter.<br>
<br>
“Hey, are you awake?” Chloe asked as the volunteer wheeled her into the room. Lex smiled and then winced at the pain.<br>
<br>
“Yeah. It’s time for another dose of medication. It’s kind of hard to sleep without them,” he answered. She nodded and gave him a sympathetic look. “Mr. Sullivan,” he said, acknowledging her father’s presence.<br>
<br>
“Mr. Luthor,” he greeted back. Lex looked like a truck had hit him. ‘Or a tractor,’ Gabe thought to himself. Lex took in Chloe’s appearance.<br>
<br>
“You’re leaving?” He asked.<br>
<br>
“Yep,” she said cheerfully. “No more poison in my system. I’m still queasy, not dizzy though, and they said that the nausea should go away in a few months.”<br>
<br>
“Great,” Lex said sarcastically. “You weren’t eating enough as it was.” Gabe appeared thoughtful at Lex’s comment. That’s not the sort of thing that you notice if you don’t care about someone.<br>
<br>
~*~*~*~*~<br>
<br>
“Hello?” Clark answered the phone while his parents tried to decide on an apt punishment for him.<br>
<br>
“Hi Clark,” Lana’s voice came through the receiver. She didn’t sound happy. “What is this I hear about you sending Lex to the hospital?”<br>
<br>
“Clark? Are you going to answer me?” Lana asked after a brief lapse in the conversation.<br>
<br>
“Yes,” he finally said.<br>
<br>
“Yes?”<br>
<br>
“Yes, I hit Lex and he had to go to the hospital,” Clark confirmed begrudgingly. He didn’t want to talk to Lana about this. He didn’t need another person to be angry with him. Why couldn’t it have been Pete who called? Then he would have been getting a pat on the back. He heard Lana sigh.<br>
<br>
“Clark, you do realize that you’ve just pushed Chloe further into his arms right?” She asked. “I thought the goal here was to get her away from him,” she continued without waiting for a response.<br>
<br>
“Lana, you don’t know everything that’s going on,” Clark said, feebly trying to stick up for himself.<br>
<br>
“Chloe’s pregnant,” she responded in a somewhat arrogant tone. Clark was confused.<br>
<br>
“How did you know that?”<br>
<br>
“Same way I knew that you hit Lex, I have a source at the hospital,” she said proudly.<br>
<br>
“Oh.”<br>
<br>
“Anyway, you still didn’t answer my question,” she prodded. This time, Clark sighed.<br>
<br>
“Yes, I realize that I probably pushed her further into Lex’s arms,” he admitted. Lana grumbled something Clark couldn’t make out.<br>
<br>
“Alright Clark, I’m going to tell you something that my ‘source’ told me, but only if you use it to make amends with Chloe. Understood?” She was starting to get frustrated with Clark’s incompetence when it came to matters of the heart. He perked up a little at the information. If there was something that could help him, he wanted to know what it was.<br>
<br>
“What is it?”<br>
<br>
“Chloe was released this morning,” she said. “But Lex won’t be released for another week or so.” Her voice was chipper. If a week apart from Lex didn’t make Chloe wake up and see Clark standing right in front of her, then fine, she deserved Lex. Lana wondered if the rumor her friend had told her about Lex impregnating Chloe on purpose was true, but she figured it would only upset Clark if she asked him if he knew.<br>
<br>
“Really?” He asked hopefully. His inner voice was cheering him on.<br>
<br>
“Yeah, so go over there and do something about it,” she said.<br>
<br>
“I will, thanks Lana.” He had a genuine smile on his face for the first time in what seemed like forever. Or, at least since he found out that Lex got Chloe pregnant. His parents walked back into the room.<br>
<br>
“Alright Clark, we’ve decided on a punishment,” his mom announced. He cringed. This couldn’t be good. He looked at them expectantly.<br>
<br>
“Grounded. One month,” his dad said. Martha looked at Jonathan. “And extra chores around the farm for the duration.” Clark groaned. How was he supposed to see Chloe if he was grounded?<br>
<br>
“Something wrong?” Martha raised her eyebrow and crossed her arms, challenging him to contest what they had said. He shook his head.<br>
<br>
“Chloe was released this morning. I was just hoping to go apologize to her,” he said. He hoped they bought the apology bit. Clark did want to say he was sorry, but that obviously wasn’t his primary motivation for wanting to see Chloe. His mom’s expression softened a little.<br>
<br>
“Well,” she started and looked at Jonathan. He nodded. “I guess that would be alright. But no going out with your other friends or anything like that.” Clark smiled and nodded.<br>
<br>
“No problem, thanks Mom, Dad,” he said as he ran out the door. Jonathan rolled his eyes.<br>
<br>
“Like we could have kept him here if we wanted to.”<br>
<br>
~*~*~*~*~*~<br>
<br>
Gabe answered the door and smiled widely when he saw that it was Clark.<br>
<br>
“Hi Clark,” he greeted. “Come on in.” Clark walked past him and pushed his hands into his pockets.<br>
<br>
“Lana told me that Chloe was released this morning,” Clark said. “I thought I’d come by and say hi.” Gabe nodded.<br>
<br>
“She’s taking a nap, but I don’t think she’ll mind if you wake her up,” Gabe responded with a smile. He liked Clark. Clark knew everything about Chloe and Lex and was still willing to be her friend, or more. Clark made his way to her room and watched her sleep for a moment before nudging her.<br>
<br>
“Chloe,” he said quietly. She stirred and opened her eyes. Her vision was a little blurry, but she could make out that it was Clark.<br>
<br>
“Clark?” She asked and sat up in her bed rubbing her eyes. “What are you doing here?” He smiled and sat on her bed.<br>
<br>
“I just wanted to say I’m sorry for everything,” he said. Chloe looked surprised. On the way over to her house, he had developed a new strategy to get her back. He would tell her what she wanted to hear until he was back in her good graces, they would start spending more time together, and then it would just be a matter of time.<br>
<br>
“Really?” She asked, a skeptical tone to her voice. He smiled again and looked down.<br>
<br>
“Yeah, I just overreacted. You know?” He saw Chloe nod and he grinned. “So, you think you can forgive me?” He partially looked up, his face wearing a puppy dog expression. She smiled and touched his hand.<br>
<br>
“Of course Clark. I’m sorry too.” They both leaned in and gave each other a big hug. Clark stood up and ran a hand through his hair.<br>
<br>
“I need to get home, I just wanted to say that I was sorry,” he said. Chloe nodded.<br>
<br>
“I’m glad you came over.”<br>
<br>
“Me too,” Clark said. ‘Me too.’ Clark left Chloe’s house feeling confident of his future with her. Chloe’s cell phone rang five minutes after Clark had gone.<br>
<br>
“Hello?” She answered.<br>
<br>
“Hey,” Lex greeted. She smiled at the sound of his voice. “So I was thinking…”<br>
<br>
“Good for you sweetie,” she jested. Lex chuckled.<br>
<br>
“I can’t believe you still have that wit on you after being in the hospital. The poison didn’t get rid of any of it?” He teased.<br>
<br>
“None,” she answered. “So what were you thinking about?”<br>
<br>
“Right. What I was thinking about. I know you’re only sixteen, but when are we doing the whole marriage thing?”<br>
