“Um, we’re not,” she replied in a quiet voice. She could almost see him furrowing his brow at her.<br>
<br>
“I see,” he said in a calm voice. Much too calm Chloe thought. “Did something happen with the baby? Did you change your mind?” He was trying desperately to stay rational, but knew he was going to lose it if he lost her.<br>
<br>
“No. I just, I just can’t be married Lex,” she said. He sighed.<br>
<br>
“You’re willing to have my child but you don’t want to marry me?” He asked to clarify. “Please Chloe, for the love of God, tell me that Clark hasn’t gotten to you.”<br>
<br>
“I talked to Clark just a little bit ago, he came over to say he was sorry about everything,” Chloe said. “And, I’m not ruling out marriage eventually, just…” She shook her head. She couldn’t possibly be throwing away what might be her destiny for her dreams could she? “I don’t know what to do Lex,” she admitted. Lex could hear Chloe start crying and mentally slapped himself.<br>
<br>
‘Of course she’s not going to want a proposal like that you idiot,’ he thought. ‘Especially after a visit from Kent.’ He had to keep himself from growling. “Chloe, I’m sorry,” he said. She sniffled.<br>
<br>
“When are you getting out?” She asked, changing the topic.<br>
<br>
“Good news on that front actually, I’m being released tomorrow,” he answered.<br>
<br>
“Really?” Chloe cheered up. “I thought they would have to keep you longer than that.” Lex chuckled.<br>
<br>
“Well, therein lies one of the benefits in having money,” he said. She rolled her eyes. He stopped talking for a moment while he thought. “Chloe, do you still want to be with me?”<br>
<br>
“How can you even ask me that?” She asked him back.<br>
<br>
“I notice that you didn’t answer my question,” he observed.<br>
<br>
“Yes.”<br>
<br>
“Alright, when I get out, I want to spend more time with you then. Understood?” He asked; although Chloe took it for what it was, a demand, but she decided not to call him on it.<br>
<br>
“I think I can handle that,” she replied.<br>
<br>
“Good. I love you,” Lex said. He never would have been able to say those words to anyone else. He hoped Chloe knew how much that meant.<br>
<br>
“I love you too Lex,” she said. He smiled.<br>
<br>
“Chloe, one more thing…”<br>
<br>
“Yes?”<br>
<br>
“Don’t let Clark hang all over you until I get out,” he said with a smirk that was quickly shot down by Chloe’s response.<br>
<br>
“So after you get out it’s okay if I let him hang all over me?” She teased.<br>
<br>
“That’s not funny.” He could hear Chloe laughing and he shook his head. “I’ll see you tomorrow.” They said their good-byes and Lex sat in his hospital bed wondering what he could do to convince Chloe to marry him. He thought the pregnancy alone should be enough to at least make her consider it, but he knew how independent she was. He shook his head again. The problem wasn’t her independence. She could be with him and still retain whom she was and what she wanted to do with her life. The problem was Clark Kent. He was sure of it, and he needed to find a way to get him out of the picture for good.<br>
<br>
~*~*~*~*~*~<br>
<br>
The next day, Chloe was awake and feeling much better. Her dad had taken too much time off to be with her as it was and had to go into work, so she was alone at the house. The doorbell rang and she walked over to answer it. Lex. He looked awful, and she silently wondered how Clark could have caused so much damage by just hitting him. She carefully gave him a hug and he laughed.<br>
<br>
“I’m not going to break you know,” he half-whispered into her ear. Shivers coursed through her body and she tried to shake them off.<br>
<br>
“Don’t do that,” she said a little too gruffly.<br>
<br>
“Something wrong?” He asked. She walked over to the couch and he followed her.<br>
<br>
“Right now is not the time to be thinking lusty thoughts about you,” she said, and then realized that it had been out loud when she saw the smile on his face. Chloe blushed and tried to face the other way. “Sorry.” He turned her face back around.<br>
<br>
“It’s okay. I’ll be better soon. Feel free to think all the lusty thoughts you want about me,” he smirked and she grinned. He paused and leaned closer to her, moving some stray hairs behind her ear. “How long do you need?” He asked seriously. She looked at him.<br>
<br>
“For what?” She asked.<br>
<br>
“Until you love me enough to say yes,” he said quietly. His voice was quivering and he didn’t want her to hear it.<br>
<br>
“I already love you enough to say yes,” she said, copying his volume. “That’s the problem.”<br>
<br>
“It doesn’t sound like a problem,” he replied. He moved his head to nuzzle against her neck and she closed her eyes.<br>
<br>
“And if you were in my position?” She asked, searching for an answer that could help her understand all of the emotions she was having. Lex pulled back and looked thoughtful.<br>
<br>
“Thank God you’re not me,” he finally said, a grin tugging at his lips. She laughed. “You’re afraid you’ll lose yourself, your identity,” he guessed. She nodded.<br>
<br>
“I don’t want to give up my dreams,” she said, holding back the tears that were forming in her eyes.<br>
<br>
“You don’t have to,” he said reassuringly. He moved to kneel down in front of her. He took her hands in his. “Marry me,” he said. It sounded remarkably unlike a question. She gazed at him for a long time before answering. She stared at every feature on his face, including the bandages and the bruising that was creeping out from underneath them. They had both been through so much and were still so young. Chloe finally gave her answer. She nodded.<br>
<br>
“Yes,” she said. After all, who was she to reject destiny?<br>
