“Chloe,” Lex said. He leaned up against the closed door. “Are you sure you wouldn’t rather have a big wedding with all your friends and family there?”<br>
<br>
“I’m sure,” she responded from the other side of the door, and then laughed. “Can you imagine how many people would stand up to object?” Lex looked thoughtful.<br>
<br>
“Good point,” he agreed.<br>
<br>
“Exactly. It took how long to convince my dad to sign the paperwork allowing this? There’s just no way that we could have a big wedding.”<br>
<br>
“So are you going to come out any time today? The judge is waiting in the living room,” he said impatiently.<br>
<br>
“Fine. Go wait with him,” she replied.<br>
<br>
“Chloe,” he pleaded in the sweetest tone he could muster, but it came out kind of whiney.<br>
<br>
“You’re not supposed to see me before the ceremony anyway. I’ll meet you there in a couple of minutes,” she said, smoothing down her dress with her hands. He sighed loudly so she could hear it and then walked away. She briefly smiled to herself at his behavior. She did wish that her dad could be there, Clark and Pete too, maybe even Lana, but she knew none of them would agree with what they were doing. She wasn’t entirely sure she agreed with it herself, but she had to take the risk. She opened the door and walked toward the living room. She saw Lex standing there talking to the judge and she returned the judge’s smile when he looked over at her.<br>
<br>
Lex turned to follow the judge’s gaze and a wide smile crossed his face. He held out his hand for her to come and stand next to him. She wore a simple, yet elegant, ivory silk dress with beading, and pearls in her hair.<br>
<br>
“Lucky man,” the judge nudged Lex.<br>
<br>
~*~*~*~*~<br>
<br>
The bell for the kitchen entrance rang and one of the kitchen staff answered it. She smiled at Clark Kent, who was holding the first of many boxes of produce. She motioned for him to come in.<br>
<br>
“Lex having another party?” He asked as he set the first box down. He was friendly with all of the kitchen staff at this point, and he knew they wouldn’t think he was prying for information. The woman smiled and signed the slip of paper Clark handed to her.<br>
<br>
“Mr. Luthor is getting married today. He wants us to prepare a feast for him and his new wife,” she said as if it was nothing. Clark furrowed his brow.<br>
<br>
“Married?” He asked. “Guess I didn’t get my invitation,” he tried to appear nonchalant about it as he brought another box in.<br>
<br>
“No one got invitations,” she commented and looked through the produce approvingly. “It’s a private ceremony and there’s no reception. Damn shame if you ask me. With all his money they could have had a royal wedding, but Chloe said it was fine with her if they just eloped, and of course Mr. Luthor jumped all over that.” She rolled her eyes. Clark’s mouth was hanging open in shock.<br>
<br>
“Ch-Chloe?” He stammered. She nodded.<br>
<br>
“She said to call her by her first name, nice girl, full of spunk.” She looked at Clark. The color had drained from his face. “Are you alright son?” He shook his head.<br>
<br>
“What time are they getting married?” He managed to get out.<br>
<br>
“Right about now I imagine. The judge got here about a half hour ago.” She glanced up from looking at the produce and Clark was gone. She shook her head. “Strange boy.”<br>
<br>
~*~*~*~*~<br>
<br>
Clark ran to the living room and saw Lex and Chloe, his Chloe, standing there with the judge.<br>
<br>
“I object!” He yelled. They turned to face him. Chloe looked stunned that he was even there, let alone objecting to the wedding. Lex, on the other hand, remained surprisingly calm.<br>
<br>
“We’ve already passed that part Clark,” he said in a smooth voice that only fueled Clark’s anger with him. The judge looked thoughtful.<br>
<br>
“Well, actually…” he began, but quickly shut up when Lex glared at him. Clark smirked.<br>
<br>
“You can’t perform the wedding if I object can you?” He asked in recognition. Lex clenched his hands into fists. The judge looked at Lex expectantly. They had already said their vows. Truth be told, all he needed to do was pronounce them man and wife, although he hesitated to do so with the current objection.<br>
<br>
“I just need to find out the reason for the objection and if it’s valid enough to keep from marrying them,” the judge replied. Clark nodded and walked over to them. He couldn’t stop looking at Chloe and Lex cringed. He didn’t like the way Clark was openly leering at his soon to be wife. The judge cleared his throat to get Clark’s attention. Clark looked up. “The reason?”<br>
<br>
“She doesn’t love him, she’s only marrying him because he got her pregnant, and he did that intentionally without her knowledge,” Clark rambled, still eyeing Chloe. Lex had to applaud her efforts to not let this disruption upset her. She seemed to still be standing tall, although be it with an angry look on her face. The judge’s face paled and he shook his head to clear it.<br>
<br>
“What?” He asked, making sure he had heard the young man correctly. He turned to Lex. “Is this true?”<br>
<br>
“Which part?” Lex replied, causing a more discomfort to cross the judge’s features.<br>
<br>
“Any of it,” he said. Lex tried to keep from rolling her eyes.<br>
<br>
“Chloe does love me,” he glanced at Chloe for affirmation and she smiled and nodded. “She probably is only marrying me because I got her pregnant, but to my knowledge, quite a few marriages begin that way.” The judge nodded.<br>
<br>
“And the third?” He asked. Lex sighed and ran his hand over the back of his neck.<br>
<br>
“Not true. He assumed and I didn’t correct his assumption,” Lex answered. The judge let out a breath. Lex Luthor was a powerful man, and he had no desire to die. On the other hand, Luthor was also known for not being entirely truthful, and if the allegations were correct, he couldn’t let the young woman marry him.<br>
<br>
“I see,” he finally said. “In that case, Mr. Luthor, will you please take Ms. Sullivan’s hand.” Lex reached out for her and Clark saw that their rings had already been exchanged. “With the power invested in me by the state of Kansas, I now pronounce you man and wife. You may kiss your bride.” Lex pulled Chloe to him and kissed her softly, so as not to cause any pain in his jaw. Clark stumbled backward for a moment, shaking his head in disbelief, but then he saw the smile on Chloe’s face. He came over to her, despite a growl from Lex and gave her a warm hug.<br>
<br>
“I’ll always be here if you need me,” he whispered in her ear and then kissed her cheek. Clark left the manor that day with a deep sense of regret. He would never again hesitate to act on something so important before it was too late.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
